				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tunedtoadeadchannel" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(304457); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=304457&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182942" alt="tunedtoadeadchannel" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=304457)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tunedtoadeadchannel" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(304457); return false;" >tunedtoadeadchannel</a></span> <span class="odate time_1275239768 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 May 2010 17:16</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-796863">
									

<p>Okay. I liked this. Halfway through, I upvoted, because the concept is cool and to a layman like myself the sciencebabble is beievable and not overpowering. A few sections, specifically throwaway lines about treatment of foetuses and "undesireable recessive genes" were excellent.</p>
<p>Then…</p>
<p>I got to the logs.</p>
<p>The logs there take a really sweet pod people-esque "they are dangerous and walk among us" vibe with a viable hook and turn it into a cliche ridden <em>Underground Vampyre Societie</em> meets the morrowind beholder's cult <em>thing</em> that is meh in the extreme. Everything from the narmy "oh, it must be safe here AAAAAAGH" beginning section to the <em>exceedingly</em> predictable "Oh, I thought you were dead. Oh well, welcome back AAAAAAAGH" ending screamed dissapointing, and the line about "the master" actually made me facepalm.</p>
<p>That's right, alias. I facepalmed, in real life. I wasn't ready for it, and I knocked my glasses off, and it hurt, and it's all your fault. Feel bad.</p>
<p>But seriously, the concept here is good, and the description is excellent. Everything but the logs is great and upvote worthy. I reccomend you heavily rewrite or just remove the loggy transcript bits, because then I will upvote this and perhaps manage not to bruise my own forehead next time I read it.</p>

							</div>

								
